-- Danish consumer confidence fell to 6.0 points in Dec
-- 
-- Mon Dec 22, 2014 03:08AM EST
-- None



COPENHAGEN, Dec 22 (Reuters) - Denmark's consumer confidence index fell to 6.0 points in December from 6.3 points in November, the statistics office said on Monday.

Dec 2014Nov 2014   Full-year 2013  Consumer confidence6.0 6.3  1.4  The monthly survey asks a cross section of Denmark's population its views on current personal and national economic trends, along with consumer intentions for the coming months.